body.name: A Seller’s Market: A Young Jesse McDermitt Novel (Tropical Adventure Series Book 1)
body.description: Six months out of high school and just days after finishing Marine boot camp, Jesse McDermitt is finally ready to unwind and have a little fun when he goes home on leave.But everything Jesse remembers—his friends, his family, the sparkling beaches and familiar waters of the Caloosahatchee River and Pine Island Sound, even his faithful Lab, Molly, have all changed.Only when he reunites with a boot camp buddy to explore the reefs of the Florida Keys and the oddly relaxing shallows of the backcountry does Jesse finally understand that it was he, himself, who had changed.The two young men, enjoying life in paradise while on boot camp leave, soon find out that there are still pirates in those tropical waters. Only their galleons and corsairs have been replaced with offshore racing boats and motorcycles.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 14, 2024
reviews.reviewText: A great story of young Jesse McDermitt. Most storytellers have characters but this time he was up close and personal. Great read.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 19, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This was so fun to read! Thank you, Wayne, for introducing young Jesse and Rusty to us. I've read all of the Jesse books and anxiously await the next one. Now I have two to look forward to, plus Charity. I too am a long time Parrothead and was so sad when he passed. His music and memories of times shared with friends listening to him and going to his shows are some of the best memories of my life. We even decided to honor him when we got a new car a week or so after he passed so if you see a license plate that says JB 9123, you'll know it's one of your's and Jimmy's biggest fans.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 15, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Its so hard to think of Jesse as only 17 in this book when I just read the latest of Jesse the 65 year old. I wishwe could have grown up together. ( Jesse and I) I've read all of the Jesse series except one or two. Wayne is a great author and how he can come up with all the scenarios is amazing. One wonders if he himself has experienced all of that.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 3, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Good story of Jesse and rusty in the early years thought it started slow but picked up once out of boot camp looking forward to reading more of the early days..

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 26, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Great work Wayne, looking forward to Jesse27. I’ve read 1-26 more than once and will continue as I read something new in his adventures every time

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 23, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A great reverse start.
reviews.reviewText: A great start to a very enjoyable series. Wayne's character development and writing skills are among the best. I look forward to more stories in the future.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 1, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A Marine Is Born
reviews.reviewText: I hesitated reading this book because I could not get my head wrapped around Jesse as a child. So here I am happy as a clam that I started this book a few nights ago and savored each word line and chapter and could not wait until my next quiet evening to once again witness young Jesse as he grows into the amazing man I have come to know so many books ago. Thank you Mr. Stinnett for all the wonderful hours you have given me as I turn the pages anticipating the next adventure!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 6, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars A little to preachy for my taste
reviews.reviewText: I think the concept "do the right thing" was stated about 20 different ways in this book. Other than that, this was a pretty good story. I think the portrayal of Jesse as a young man fit reasonably well. However, at least for me, the portrayal of Rusty just didn't fit what I would have imagined.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on September 29, 2023
reviews.reviewText: What is it about Wayne, not content with writing a very successful Jesse McDermitt novels with another few very good off suits he then takes the reader right back to the start of his career with the Marines and intertwines the story with all that you enjoy reading this type of genre and in my book it encapsulates everything that I love with Wayne.Even if you haven't read any of his books, this will surely whet your appetite. Can't wait for the next book.
